      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">31/8/87 ¶  ¶ Your Tillaea interests me much, dear Mr Deane, and it seems quite new; thus I will name it after you; ¶  it is nearest to T. macrantha &amp; to a S. African species. Kindly send me some more ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.08.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Deane</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 577, folder 30, series 4, MS 610 Deane family papers, National Library of Australia, Canberra.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>31/8/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Tillaea interests me much, dear Mr Deane, and it seems quite new; thus I will name it after you;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M did not describe a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Tillaea deani</seg>.</p>
               </note> it is nearest to T. macrantha &amp; to a S. African species. Kindly send me some more specimens when the fruits are ripening, so I can compare the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">seeds</hi>
               </seg> critically. I am just sending the msc<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">manuscript.</p>
               </note> of the "Key I" to the press, so that a copy can likely be sent you in October.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please look for Aldronanda as perhaps there or in Riverina entangled among floating Utriculoriae</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Have you no friends in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Central</hi>
               </seg> Austr, who at this marvellous season would collect <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg> sorts of plants, particularly also the minute <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">spring</hi>
               </seg>-<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annuals</hi>
               </seg> and saltbushes, and send dried branchlets in flower or <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruit</hi>
               </seg> by successive mails.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">The p/c has a note: notes say there was a sketch with this letter. Scan in if found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
